A
B
n\times n
\det(AB) = \det (A)\det (B)
|A| = 2,\;|B| = n \implies \det(AB) = 2n = \det A\cdot \det B 
|A| = 0,\;|B| = n \implies \det(AB) = 0 = 0\cdot n = \det A\cdot \det B
\det(AB) = 0 \implies (\det A = 0 \;\;\text{OR}\;\;\det B = 0).
